davis devises new borrowing plan his executive order could speed up $0.0 billion in bond sales and bypass puc oversight of repayment mechanism
sacramento
gov
gray davis is crafting a new plan to expedite the long-delayed borrowing of $0.0 billion to repay the sagging california state budget for emergency electricity it bought during the energy crisis
the plan
which could be contained in an executive order as early as next week
would minimize the role of the state's top power regulator
the public utilities commission
which enraged davis last week when it declined to sign off on his original plan
with enough power now under contract to avert blackouts and plans in place for the recovery of the two state's largest utilities
the repayment to the state treasury would resolve one of the last remaining issues of the energy crisis
that is one scenario
davis spokeswoman hilary mclean said wednesday when asked about the proposal
