the ability of large businesses to bypass utilities and contract directly with generators for power
will shift higher costs to smaller customers
the puc proposed the ban on direct access in june but didn't adopt the policy until sept
0
during that period
the amount of energy large consumers contracted for through direct access increased from 0 percent to 0 percent
what's happened here is one of the most damaging things that has happened to consumers during the energy crisis
