with the current glut of contracts
why do we need additional reserves
kellan flukinger
senior advisor to chairman freeman and laura doll
provided a detailed presentation explaining why he believes the power authority must contract for additional renewable and peaking generation
flukinger believes that despite direct access and the current glut of electricity supplied in long-term contracts
