flukinger concluded that the state still is at the mercy of electric generators who are not subject to puc regulatory authority and who have no real obligation to build and maintain new facilities or to serve customers within the state
he believes that the short-term contracts and spot purchases leave the state vulnerable to price-spikes and supply shortages
